{"word":"μήτρως","slug":"μήτρως","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>μήτρως</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:plural'>pl.</a> always of the third decl., like <a href='S:πάτρως'><el>πάτρως</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>a maternal uncle</i>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>any relation by the mother's side</i>, <b><a href='S:Pindar'>Pind.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>3. </b>= <a href='S:μητροπάτωρ'><el>μητροπάτωρ</el></a>, <b><a href='S:Pindar'>Pind.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}